<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="475" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1389,2027]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,150,501]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="475" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1533,1559]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." box="[321,656,1533,1560]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova &amp; Koroleva (1964)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[878,971,1533,1559]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Pseudoparasitus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sellnicki">
<emphasis box="[878,971,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">sellnicki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name for 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">haemisphaericus</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J. &amp; Sandmann, J. &amp; Klarner, B. &amp; Widyastuti, R. &amp; Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S." box="[203,448,1569,1595]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref7827" refString="Beaulieu, F., Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J., Sandmann, J., Klarner, B., Widyastuti, R., Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S. (2019) Review of the mite genus Ololaelaps (Acari, Laelapidae) and redescription of O. formidabilis Berlese. ZooKeys, 853, 1 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 853.29407" type="journal article" year="2019">
Beaulieu 
<emphasis box="[310,359,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
have comprehensively discussed the confusion surrounding the name 
<emphasis box="[1239,1429,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">haemisphaericus</emphasis>
. We here designate a 
<typeStatus box="[385,488,1605,1631]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">lectotype</typeStatus>
in order to maintain the prevailing concept of the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[1124,1217,1605,1631]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Pseudoparasitus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sellnicki">
<emphasis box="[1124,1217,1605,1631]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">sellnicki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J. &amp; Sandmann, J. &amp; Klarner, B. &amp; Widyastuti, R. &amp; Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S." pageId="9" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref7827" refString="Beaulieu, F., Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J., Sandmann, J., Klarner, B., Widyastuti, R., Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S. (2019) Review of the mite genus Ololaelaps (Acari, Laelapidae) and redescription of O. formidabilis Berlese. ZooKeys, 853, 1 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 853.29407" type="journal article" year="2019">
Beaulieu 
<emphasis box="[1373,1422,1605,1631]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
., 2019
</bibRefCitation>
suggested). This species is widely distributed in western parts of Eurasia (
<bibRefCitation author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J. &amp; Sandmann, J. &amp; Klarner, B. &amp; Widyastuti, R. &amp; Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S." box="[1036,1274,1641,1667]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref7827" refString="Beaulieu, F., Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J., Sandmann, J., Klarner, B., Widyastuti, R., Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S. (2019) Review of the mite genus Ololaelaps (Acari, Laelapidae) and redescription of O. formidabilis Berlese. ZooKeys, 853, 1 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 853.29407" type="journal article" year="2019">
Beaulieu 
<emphasis box="[1144,1193,1641,1667]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
., 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). We here provide additional morphological characters to complement the original description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." box="[1082,1436,1677,1704]" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova and Koroleva (1964)</bibRefCitation>
by examining type series specimens, all these observations were made on all specimens examined, unless specified: (1) dorsal shield essentially smooth, without reticulation (i.e. not reticulate, but completely micropunctate) over whole surface, bearing 37 pairs of setae (
<emphasis box="[631,656,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">z1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[716,740,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">z3</emphasis>
absent in all examined specimens) (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1249,1785,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 31, general view dorsally; 32, general view ventrally; 33, idiosoma in ventral view; 34, sternal shield; 35, subcapitulum; 36, part of hologastric shield; 37, details of peritrematal shield, showing fusion of peritrematal-hologastric-parapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet, the epipleuron section (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 38, chelicera; 39, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571768/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
), a supernumerary seta 
<emphasis box="[250,275,1822,1847]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Jx</emphasis>
present between 
<emphasis box="[477,489,1822,1847]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">J</emphasis>
-series, ventrolateral margins (epipleura) smooth and narrow, much less developed than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[236,393,1857,1883]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[236,256,1857,1883]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[270,393,1858,1883]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and [whatever other spp. with broad epipleura] (
<figureCitation box="[942,1095,1857,1883]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 31, general view dorsally; 32, general view ventrally; 33, idiosoma in ventral view; 34, sternal shield; 35, subcapitulum; 36, part of hologastric shield; 37, details of peritrematal shield, showing fusion of peritrematal-hologastric-parapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet, the epipleuron section (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 38, chelicera; 39, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571768/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Figs 32 &amp; 33</figureCitation>
); (2) metasternal setae 
<emphasis box="[1356,1388,1857,1883]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">st4</emphasis>
and metasternal poroids obviously inserted on the sternal shield margin (
<figureCitation box="[937,1024,1893,1919]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 31, general view dorsally; 32, general view ventrally; 33, idiosoma in ventral view; 34, sternal shield; 35, subcapitulum; 36, part of hologastric shield; 37, details of peritrematal shield, showing fusion of peritrematal-hologastric-parapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet, the epipleuron section (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 38, chelicera; 39, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571768/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
); (3) fused peritrematal-hologastricparapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet; hologastric shield strongly reticulated, anteriorly comprising polygonal cells, cells elongated transversally in region anterior to anus, bearing four pairs of slender setae, 
<emphasis box="[1350,1389,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Jv3</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,194,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Zv2</emphasis>
off the shield (
<figureCitation box="[361,574,2001,2027]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 31, general view dorsally; 32, general view ventrally; 33, idiosoma in ventral view; 34, sternal shield; 35, subcapitulum; 36, part of hologastric shield; 37, details of peritrematal shield, showing fusion of peritrematal-hologastric-parapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet, the epipleuron section (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 38, chelicera; 39, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571768/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="473">Figs 32, 33, 36, 37</figureCitation>
); (4) hypostomal groove with six transverse rows of denticles, each row with 4–7 small denticles, groove wider anteriorly, progressively narrowing from anterior to posterior (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1318,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 31, general view dorsally; 32, general view ventrally; 33, idiosoma in ventral view; 34, sternal shield; 35, subcapitulum; 36, part of hologastric shield; 37, details of peritrematal shield, showing fusion of peritrematal-hologastric-parapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet, the epipleuron section (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 38, chelicera; 39, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571768/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
); (5) fixed digit of chelicera with an offset subapical tooth (gabelzahn), followed by two moderately large teeth; movable digit with two similarly large sized teeth (
<figureCitation box="[570,654,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 31, general view dorsally; 32, general view ventrally; 33, idiosoma in ventral view; 34, sternal shield; 35, subcapitulum; 36, part of hologastric shield; 37, details of peritrematal shield, showing fusion of peritrematal-hologastric-parapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet, the epipleuron section (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 38, chelicera; 39, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571768/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
); (6) the pretarsal paradactyli on legs II–IV are elongated, with their tips projecting well beyond the claws (
<figureCitation box="[589,674,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[197,1391,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 31, general view dorsally; 32, general view ventrally; 33, idiosoma in ventral view; 34, sternal shield; 35, subcapitulum; 36, part of hologastric shield; 37, details of peritrematal shield, showing fusion of peritrematal-hologastric-parapodal shields by way of the metapodal platelet, the epipleuron section (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 38, chelicera; 39, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571768/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
); (7) spermathecae well-sclerotised and with a distinctive subapical appendage (in four examined specimens) as showed in 
<figureCitation box="[761,871,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–42" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1634,1658]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,525,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-197@11.[165,1423,525,1610]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 40–42. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 40, spermathecal structures; male (paralectotype). 41, chelicera; 42, tarsus II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571770/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">Figure 40</figureCitation>
; (8) spermatodactyl with a sinuous duct, and a subapical bend (
<figureCitation box="[294,377,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–42" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1634,1658]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,525,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-197@11.[165,1423,525,1610]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 40–42. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 40, spermathecal structures; male (paralectotype). 41, chelicera; 42, tarsus II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571770/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
); (9) tarsus II in male bearing a spine-like ventral seta (
<emphasis box="[994,1034,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">pv2</emphasis>
) (see 
<figureCitation box="[1102,1185,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–42" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1634,1658]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,525,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-197@11.[165,1423,525,1610]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 40–42. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps sellnicki Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 40, spermathecal structures; male (paralectotype). 41, chelicera; 42, tarsus II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571770/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Supplementary measurements (n=4): (1) almost all dorsal setae uniform in length 32–38; (2) sternal shield length 102–106, maximum width 200–219, between coxae II 115–120; (3) hologastric shield 390–395 long (4) sternal setae (
<emphasis box="[1262,1342,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">st1–st4</emphasis>
) 57–63, metasternal setae 
<emphasis box="[353,386,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">st5</emphasis>
&amp; pre-anal setae (
<emphasis box="[599,670,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">JV1–3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[686,761,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="475">ZV1–2</emphasis>
) 39–52; (5) legs: I (568–577), II (440–450), III (412–420), IV (548–568).
</paragraph>
